The private schools in Scotland maintain a history of academic excellence, and this continued in 2018 with another collection of outstanding results in the exams, which is only reinforced by individual and collective success in sport, art, music and other community subjects.
With more than 30,000 students throughout Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Council of Private Schools (SCIS for their acronyms in English), strive to offer the highest level to students and their parents.
Private schools aim to prepare their students for higher education, for the career they choose, and for their place as citizens of the world.
As an educational sector that can design and implement a tailored curriculum, we are seeing that modern languages continue to be a popular and desired theme within schools.
Nelson Mandela said, "If you speak to a man in a language he understands, that comes to his head.
But if you speak to him in his own language, he will reach his heart."
